output:
Jingle Bells
Oh, what joy it is to ride in a one-horse open sleigh!
A day or two ago, I thought I'd take a ride,
And soon Miss Fanny Bright was seated by my side.
The horse was lean and lame, misfortune seemed his lot,
He got into a drifted bank and wee-wee got upset.
A day or two ago, the story I must tell,
I went out in snow, and on my back I fell,
A gentleman's riding me, in a one-horse open sleigh.
He laughed as I sprawling lied, but quickly drove away.
Jingle bells, jingle bells, jingle all the way,
Oh, what joy it is to ride in a one-horse open sleigh!
Now the ground is wet, go in while you're young,
Take the girls tonight, and sing the sleighing song,
Just get up off to the beat, two-forty is his speed,
Hitch him to an open sleigh, and crack, you'll take the lead.
Jingle bells, jingle bells, jingle all the way,
Oh, what joy it is to ride in a one-horse open sleigh!
Jingle bells, jingle bells, jingle all the way,
Oh, what joy it is to ride in a one-horse open sleigh!
